\title{Opentargets Database}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Query Open Targets Platform for target-disease associations, drug target discovery, tractability/safety data, genetics/omics evidence, known drugs, for therapeutic target identification."}

\subtree{
\title{Open Targets Database}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{The Open Targets Platform is a comprehensive resource for systematic identification and prioritization of potential therapeutic drug targets. It integrates publicly available datasets including human genetics, omics, literature, and chemical data to build and score target-disease associations.}

\p{\strong{Key capabilities:}}

\ul{
\li{Query target (gene) annotations including tractability, safety, expression}
\li{Search for disease-target associations with evidence scores}
\li{Retrieve evidence from multiple data types (genetics, pathways, literature, etc.)}
\li{Find known drugs for diseases and their mechanisms}
\li{Access drug information including clinical trial phases and adverse events}
\li{Evaluate target druggability and therapeutic potential}
}

\p{\strong{Data access:} The platform provides a GraphQL API, web interface, data downloads, and Google BigQuery access. This skill focuses on the GraphQL API for programmatic access.}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\p{This skill should be used when:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Target discovery:} Finding potential therapeutic targets for a disease}
\li{\strong{Target assessment:} Evaluating tractability, safety, and druggability of genes}
\li{\strong{Evidence gathering:} Retrieving supporting evidence for target-disease associations}
\li{\strong{Drug repurposing:} Identifying existing drugs that could be repurposed for new indications}
\li{\strong{Competitive intelligence:} Understanding clinical precedence and drug development landscape}
\li{\strong{Target prioritization:} Ranking targets based on genetic evidence and other data types}
\li{\strong{Mechanism research:} Investigating biological pathways and gene functions}
\li{\strong{Biomarker discovery:} Finding genes differentially expressed in disease}
\li{\strong{Safety assessment:} Identifying potential toxicity concerns for drug targets}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Workflow}
\subtree{
\title{1. Search for Entities}
\p{Start by finding the identifiers for targets, diseases, or drugs of interest.}

\p{\strong{For targets (genes):}}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_opentargets import search_entities

# Search by gene symbol or name
results = search_entities("BRCA1", entity_types=["target"])
# Returns: [{"id": "ENSG00000012048", "name": "BRCA1", ...}]
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{For diseases:}}

\pre{\startverb
# Search by disease name
results = search_entities("alzheimer", entity_types=["disease"])
# Returns: [{"id": "EFO_0000249", "name": "Alzheimer disease", ...}]
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{For drugs:}}

\pre{\startverb
# Search by drug name
results = search_entities("aspirin", entity_types=["drug"])
# Returns: [{"id": "CHEMBL25", "name": "ASPIRIN", ...}]
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Identifiers used:}}

\ul{
\li{Targets: Ensembl gene IDs (e.g., \code{\startverb ENSG00000157764\stopverb})}
\li{Diseases: EFO (Experimental Factor Ontology) IDs (e.g., \code{\startverb EFO_0000249\stopverb})}
\li{Drugs: ChEMBL IDs (e.g., \code{\startverb CHEMBL25\stopverb})}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Query Target Information}
\p{Retrieve comprehensive target annotations to assess druggability and biology.}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_opentargets import get_target_info

target_info = get_target_info("ENSG00000157764", include_diseases=True)

# Access key fields:
# - approvedSymbol: HGNC gene symbol
# - approvedName: Full gene name
# - tractability: Druggability assessments across modalities
# - safetyLiabilities: Known safety concerns
# - geneticConstraint: Constraint scores from gnomAD
# - associatedDiseases: Top disease associations with scores
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Key annotations to review:}}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Tractability:} Small molecule, antibody, PROTAC druggability predictions}
\li{\strong{Safety:} Known toxicity concerns from multiple databases}
\li{\strong{Genetic constraint:} pLI and LOEUF scores indicating essentiality}
\li{\strong{Disease associations:} Diseases linked to the target with evidence scores}
}

\p{Refer to \code{\startverb references/target_annotations.md\stopverb} for detailed information about all target features.}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Query Disease Information}
\p{Get disease details and associated targets/drugs.}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_opentargets import get_disease_info

disease_info = get_disease_info("EFO_0000249", include_targets=True)

# Access fields:
# - name: Disease name
# - description: Disease description
# - therapeuticAreas: High-level disease categories
# - associatedTargets: Top targets with association scores
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Retrieve Target-Disease Evidence}
\p{Get detailed evidence supporting a target-disease association.}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_opentargets import get_target_disease_evidence

# Get all evidence
evidence = get_target_disease_evidence(
    ensembl_id="ENSG00000157764",
    efo_id="EFO_0000249"
)

# Filter by evidence type
genetic_evidence = get_target_disease_evidence(
    ensembl_id="ENSG00000157764",
    efo_id="EFO_0000249",
    data_types=["genetic_association"]
)

# Each evidence record contains:
# - datasourceId: Specific data source (e.g., "gwas_catalog", "chembl")
# - datatypeId: Evidence category (e.g., "genetic_association", "known_drug")
# - score: Evidence strength (0-1)
# - studyId: Original study identifier
# - literature: Associated publications
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Major evidence types:}}

\ol{
\li{\strong{genetic_association:} GWAS, rare variants, ClinVar, gene burden}
\li{\strong{somatic_mutation:} Cancer Gene Census, IntOGen, cancer biomarkers}
\li{\strong{known_drug:} Clinical precedence from approved/clinical drugs}
\li{\strong{affected_pathway:} CRISPR screens, pathway analyses, gene signatures}
\li{\strong{rna_expression:} Differential expression from Expression Atlas}
\li{\strong{animal_model:} Mouse phenotypes from IMPC}
\li{\strong{literature:} Text-mining from Europe PMC}
}

\p{Refer to \code{\startverb references/evidence_types.md\stopverb} for detailed descriptions of all evidence types and interpretation guidelines.}
}

\subtree{
\title{5. Find Known Drugs}
\p{Identify drugs used for a disease and their targets.}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_opentargets import get_known_drugs_for_disease

drugs = get_known_drugs_for_disease("EFO_0000249")

# drugs contains:
# - uniqueDrugs: Total number of unique drugs
# - uniqueTargets: Total number of unique targets
# - rows: List of drug-target-indication records with:
#   - drug: {name, drugType, maximumClinicalTrialPhase}
#   - targets: Genes targeted by the drug
#   - phase: Clinical trial phase for this indication
#   - status: Trial status (active, completed, etc.)
#   - mechanismOfAction: How drug works
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Clinical phases:}}

\ul{
\li{Phase 4: Approved drug}
\li{Phase 3: Late-stage clinical trials}
\li{Phase 2: Mid-stage trials}
\li{Phase 1: Early safety trials}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{6. Get Drug Information}
\p{Retrieve detailed drug information including mechanisms and indications.}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_opentargets import get_drug_info

drug_info = get_drug_info("CHEMBL25")

# Access:
# - name, synonyms: Drug identifiers
# - drugType: Small molecule, antibody, etc.
# - maximumClinicalTrialPhase: Development stage
# - mechanismsOfAction: Target and action type
# - indications: Diseases with trial phases
# - withdrawnNotice: If withdrawn, reasons and countries
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{7. Get All Associations for a Target}
\p{Find all diseases associated with a target, optionally filtering by score.}

\pre{\startverb
from scripts.query_opentargets import get_target_associations

# Get associations with score >= 0.5
associations = get_target_associations(
    ensembl_id="ENSG00000157764",
    min_score=0.5
)

# Each association contains:
# - disease: {id, name}
# - score: Overall association score (0-1)
# - datatypeScores: Breakdown by evidence type
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Association scores:}}

\ul{
\li{Range: 0-1 (higher = stronger evidence)}
\li{Aggregate evidence across all data types using harmonic sum}
\li{NOT confidence scores but relative ranking metrics}
\li{Under-studied diseases may have lower scores despite good evidence}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{GraphQL API Details}
\p{\strong{For custom queries beyond the provided helper functions}, use the GraphQL API directly or modify \code{\startverb scripts/query_opentargets.py\stopverb}.}

\p{Key information:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Endpoint:} \code{\startverb https://api.platform.opentargets.org/api/v4/graphql\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Interactive browser:} \code{\startverb https://api.platform.opentargets.org/api/v4/graphql/browser\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{No authentication required}}
\li{\strong{Request only needed fields} to minimize response size}
\li{\strong{Use pagination} for large result sets: \code{\startverb page: {size: N, index: M}\stopverb}}
}

\p{Refer to \code{\startverb references/api_reference.md\stopverb} for:}

\ul{
\li{Complete endpoint documentation}
\li{Example queries for all entity types}
\li{Error handling patterns}
\li{Best practices for API usage}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Best Practices}
\subtree{
\title{Target Prioritization Strategy}
\p{When prioritizing drug targets:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Start with genetic evidence:} Human genetics (GWAS, rare variants) provides strongest disease relevance}
\li{\strong{Check tractability:} Prefer targets with clinical or discovery precedence}
\li{\strong{Assess safety:} Review safety liabilities, expression patterns, and genetic constraint}
\li{\strong{Evaluate clinical precedence:} Known drugs indicate druggability and therapeutic window}
\li{\strong{Consider multiple evidence types:} Convergent evidence from different sources increases confidence}
\li{\strong{Validate mechanistically:} Pathway evidence and biological plausibility}
\li{\strong{Review literature manually:} For critical decisions, examine primary publications}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Evidence Interpretation}
\p{\strong{Strong evidence indicators:}}

\ul{
\li{Multiple independent evidence sources}
\li{High genetic association scores (especially GWAS with L2G > 0.5)}
\li{Clinical precedence from approved drugs}
\li{ClinVar pathogenic variants with disease match}
\li{Mouse models with relevant phenotypes}
}

\p{\strong{Caution flags:}}

\ul{
\li{Single evidence source only}
\li{Text-mining as sole evidence (requires manual validation)}
\li{Conflicting evidence across sources}
\li{High essentiality + ubiquitous expression (poor therapeutic window)}
\li{Multiple safety liabilities}
}

\p{\strong{Score interpretation:}}

\ul{
\li{Scores rank relative strength, not absolute confidence}
\li{Under-studied diseases have lower scores despite potentially valid targets}
\li{Weight expert-curated sources higher than computational predictions}
\li{Check evidence breakdown, not just overall score}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Workflows}
\p{\strong{Workflow 1: Target Discovery for a Disease}}

\ol{
\li{Search for disease → get EFO ID}
\li{Query disease info with \code{\startverb include_targets=True\stopverb}}
\li{Review top targets sorted by association score}
\li{For promising targets, get detailed target info}
\li{Examine evidence types supporting each association}
\li{Assess tractability and safety for prioritized targets}
}

\p{\strong{Workflow 2: Target Validation}}

\ol{
\li{Search for target → get Ensembl ID}
\li{Get comprehensive target info}
\li{Check tractability (especially clinical precedence)}
\li{Review safety liabilities and genetic constraint}
\li{Examine disease associations to understand biology}
\li{Look for chemical probes or tool compounds}
\li{Check known drugs targeting gene for mechanism insights}
}

\p{\strong{Workflow 3: Drug Repurposing}}

\ol{
\li{Search for disease → get EFO ID}
\li{Get known drugs for disease}
\li{For each drug, get detailed drug info}
\li{Examine mechanisms of action and targets}
\li{Look for related disease indications}
\li{Assess clinical trial phases and status}
\li{Identify repurposing opportunities based on mechanism}
}

\p{\strong{Workflow 4: Competitive Intelligence}}

\ol{
\li{Search for target of interest}
\li{Get associated diseases with evidence}
\li{For each disease, get known drugs}
\li{Review clinical phases and development status}
\li{Identify competitors and their mechanisms}
\li{Assess clinical precedence and market landscape}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Resources}
\subtree{
\title{Scripts}
